textView.string: Want an adventurous life in Brisbane? In Australian, we would like to do some kind of adventurous activities and try to challenge ourselves. Why not just let me to lead you how to explore an adventurous trip around the famous river in Brisbane!
It was an amazing experience and I loved every minute of it. It felt great to be a part of this huge community of riders across the country, pedalling together to help these little kids.

Worthwhile experience indeed. We have climbed all three bridge climbs in the southern hemisphere and found this one equal to the others in terms of views and overall experience. You will observe 360 degree view of Brisbane from the top, with very interesting information about the city and the Story Bridge construction.

New Farm encourages an outdoor lifestyle, with tree-lined streets and unique spaces such as Brisbane Powerhouse and the heart of the suburb, New Farm Park. The park attracts visitors from near and far with its perfect riverside picnic spots, cycling loops and tree house-style adventure playground.

Challenge yourself in the great outdoors and experience climbing the weathered walls of the Kangaroo Point Cliffs. Get up close and personal and climb to the top of the 20 metre cliffs where you can take in Brisbane’s best views of the city and river! Climbs of various levels of difficulty are available to suit everyone.

Offering impressive early morning or evening views extending across the river to the city and beyond to the mountains, the cliffs are a popular picnic spot and an abseiling destination for thrill seekers. The site itself is home to the Nunukul Yuggera Tribe, whose members gather at the base of the cliffs and tell stories of the Dreamtime through song and dance.

The upper section of the Kangaroo Point Cliffs Park (River Terrace) includes the following facilities (some of which are shown on the site plan below):
- barbecues - bookings sites - cafe - open from 7am-6pm phone 07 3393 1209 - picnic tables - playground - public art - shelter - toilets - viewing platforms

textView.text: There are three designated sites for park bookings in the River Terrace section of the park.

textView.string: New Farm Park is a public park located in the suburb of New Farm, in Brisbane, Queensland, Australia. The park covers 15 hectares and is situated at the south-eastern end of the New Farm peninsula on a bend in the Brisbane River.

The upper section of the New Farm Park includes the following facilities (some of which are shown on the site plan below):
- barbecues - bookings sites - picnic tables - playground - public art - shelter - toilets - viewing platforms

Brisbane is a multi-cultural city where contains a lot of different types of arts, cultures and lifestyles for us to explore. Why not just join a small cultural trip and let me to lead you to look around the beautiful city!

Join artists and curators for a Maiwar In Conversation session at the Museum of Brisbane. Maiwar, the traditional word used to refer to the waterway now known as the Brisbane River, is a visual art exhibition of contemporary Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander artists in Council’s Vibrant Laneways Outdoor Gallery, curated by a Brisbane-based collective Blaklash.

The Collective Markets are a South Bank must-do experience while in Brisbane. They feature plenty of cool trinkets and goodies that you won't find anywhere else including arts, crafts, homewares, collectibles, exotic items, designer fashion, handmade jewellery and much more.
Afterwards, soak up a spot of live music strummed by local musicians, or retire to a nearby cafe or watering hole to watch the world continue to bustle on by.
